Senate Resolution 542
By: Senators Bearden of the 30th and Anavitarte of the 31st
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Bill Hembree; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Bill Hembree has long been recognized by the citizens of this state for the vital
3 role that he has played in leadership and his deep personal commitment to the welfare of the
4 citizens of Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, he has diligently and conscientiously devoted innumerable hours of his time,
6 talents, and energy toward the betterment of his community and state as evidenced
7 dramatically by his superlative service as founder of Bill Hembree Insurance Agency and as
8 a Representative in the Georgia House of Representatives; and
9 WHEREAS, Bill Hembree Insurance Agency, founded in 2000, has three offices located in
10 Douglasville, Marietta, and Kennesaw; and
11 WHEREAS, Bill was elected to the Georgia House of Representatives 1992, and selflessly
12 served his community until 2012; and
13 WHEREAS, in July 2022, the Bridge over Dog River, in Douglas County, Georgia, was
14 dedicated in his name in recognition of his countless contributions to the community; and
